"vadeti, “na mayaṃ caṇḍālā venā nesādā rathakārā pukkusā”ti bhaṇati … pe …."
msgstr ""
"If one who is fully ordained, wishing to revile, wishing to insult, wishing "
"to humiliate another who is fully ordained, says this, “We’re not outcasts/"
"bamboo workers/hunters/chariot-makers/waste-removers” …"

#. This looks like an editing mistake. Presumably this should read, “We’re not going to a good destination/we can only expect a bad destination.” And below <ref>MS.2.96</ref>, <ref>MS.2.104</ref>, and <ref>MS.2.108</ref>.
